        <headline>Flash Flood Warning issued July 18 at 3:08PM PDT until July 18 at 4:45PM PDT by NWS Las Vegas NV</headline>
        <description>At 308 PM PDT, Heavy rain has ended from earlier thunderstorms.
However, areas of excessive runoff will persist and elevated flows
in area washes and streams persist. Remain flood aware.

HAZARD...Life-threatening flash flooding. Thunderstorms producing
flash flooding.

SOURCE...Radar.

IMPACT...Life-threatening flash flooding of low-water crossings,
creeks, normally dry washes and roads.

Some locations that will experience flash flooding include...
Las Vegas, North Las Vegas, Lone Mountain, Centennial Hills,
Aliante, Summerlin, North Las Vegas Airport and Floyd Lamb Park.
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.</instruction>
